---
import VizLayout from "../../layouts/VizLayout.astro";
const title = "2.7 Hashing & Collision · GATE DA";
---
<VizLayout {title} currentPath="/module2/viz-2-7-hashing" pageCss="/assets/css/pages/viz-2-7-hashing.css">
  <div class="gd-breadcrumb">
    <a href="/index.html">Home</a><span>›</span>
    <a href="/module2.html">Module 2</a><span>›</span>
    2.7 Hashing &amp; Collision
  </div>
  <a class="gd-pill-link" href="/module2.html">← Module 2 Overview</a>

  <div class="gd-viz-header">
    <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;margin-bottom:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <span class="gd-badge gd-badge--subject">Module 2 · DSA</span>
      <span class="gd-badge gd-badge--pyq">h(k)=k mod m · load factor · chaining</span>
    </div>
    <h1 id="top">Hashing &amp; Collision</h1>
    <p>A good hash function spreads keys uniformly; the load factor governs how fast lookups degrade as collisions pile up.</p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="theory">Hash Functions &amp; Load Factor</h2>
  <p>
    The division-method hash is $h(k) = k \bmod m$. The <strong>load factor</strong> $\alpha = n/m$ is the ratio of stored keys to slots.
  </p>

  <div class="gd-formula-panel">
    <div class="gd-formula-label">Load factor &amp; chaining cost</div>
    <div class="gd-formula">
      $$\alpha = \frac&#123;n&#125;&#123;m&#125;, \qquad \text&#123;search (chaining)&#125; = O(1 + \alpha)$$
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="rules-grid">
    <div class="rule-card">
      <div class="rule-card__label">Chaining</div>
      <div class="gd-formula">$$O(1 + \alpha)$$</div>
      <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--gd-text-2);margin:8px 0 0;">Collisions form a linked list per slot. $\alpha$ may exceed 1.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rule-card">
      <div class="rule-card__label">Open addressing</div>
      <div class="gd-formula">$$\alpha \lt 1$$</div>
      <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--gd-text-2);margin:8px 0 0;">All keys live in the table, so it must never be full. Linear probing causes <em>primary clustering</em>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-insights">
    <div class="gd-insight gd-insight--warn">
      <span class="gd-insight__title">Primary clustering</span>
      Linear probing fills consecutive slots, so long runs grow and slow down future inserts. Double hashing scatters probes to avoid this.
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="viz1">Interactive: Hash Table with Chaining</h2>
  <p style="color:var(--gd-text-1);margin-bottom:16px;font-size:15px;">
    Enter a key and press <strong>Insert</strong>. We compute $h(k) = k \bmod 10$ and drop the key into its slot — collisions chain below.
  </p>

  <div class="gd-controls" style="margin-bottom:14px;">
    <div class="gd-controls__title">Insert key</div>
    <div style="display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:center;flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <input id="hash-key" type="number" value="73" style="width:120px;padding:8px 10px;background:var(--gd-bg-1);border:1px solid var(--gd-border);border-radius:6px;color:var(--gd-text-0);font-family:var(--gd-font-mono);">
      <button id="hash-insert" class="gd-btn gd-btn--primary">Insert</button>
      <button id="hash-reset" class="gd-btn gd-btn--secondary">Reset</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-chart">
    <div class="gd-chart__title">10-slot table — slots 0..9, chains grow downward</div>
    <div id="hash-table"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-insights">
    <div class="gd-insight gd-insight--active" id="hash-log">Enter a key and press Insert.</div>
    <div class="gd-insight" id="hash-alpha">Load factor α = n/m = 0/10 = 0.00</div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="examples">Worked Examples</h2>

  <div class="gd-example">
    <div class="gd-example__q">
      <span class="gd-example__num">Example 1 · Hash slot · NAT · ★</span>
      <p>With $h(k) = k \bmod 10$, which slot does key 73 map to?</p>
    </div>
    <div class="gd-example__body">
      <p>$73 \bmod 10 = 3$.</p>
      <div class="gd-example__ans">Slot 3.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-example">
    <div class="gd-example__q">
      <span class="gd-example__num">Example 2 · Load factor · ★</span>
      <p>A hash table has $m = 8$ slots and stores $n = 6$ keys. What is the load factor?</p>
    </div>
    <div class="gd-example__body">
      <p>$\alpha = n/m = 6/8 = 0.75$.</p>
      <div class="gd-example__ans">α = 0.75.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-gate-box">
    <div class="gd-gate-box__title">GATE DA Angle</div>
    <p><strong>Division hash:</strong> $h(k) = k \bmod m$ — compute the slot quickly.</p>
    <p><strong>Load factor:</strong> $\alpha = n/m$; chaining search is $O(1 + \alpha)$.</p>
    <p><strong>Open addressing:</strong> requires $\alpha \lt 1$; linear probing suffers primary clustering.</p>
    <p><strong>Chaining vs open addressing:</strong> chaining tolerates $\alpha \gt 1$ at the cost of pointers; open addressing is cache-friendly but degrades near full.</p>
  </div>

  <a class="gd-pill-link" href="/module2/2-7-questions.html" style="margin-top:32px;">Practice Questions →</a>
</VizLayout>

<script is:inline slot="scripts">
(function () {
  const M = 10;
  const container = document.getElementById("hash-table");
  let slots = Array.from({ length: M }, () => []);
  let n = 0;

  function draw(activeSlot, newKey) {
    if (activeSlot === undefined) activeSlot = -1;
    const slotW = 54, gap = 6, top = 30;
    const W = M * (slotW + gap);
    const maxChain = Math.max(1, ...slots.map(s => s.length));
    const H = top + 40 + maxChain * 36 + 10;
    d3.select(container).select("svg").remove();
    const svg = d3.select(container).append("svg")
      .attr("viewBox", `0 0 ${W} ${H}`)
      .style("width", "100%").style("max-width", `${W}px`).style("display", "block");

    for (let i = 0; i < M; i++) {
      const x = i * (slotW + gap);
      const isActive = i === activeSlot;
      svg.append("rect").attr("x", x).attr("y", top).attr("width", slotW).attr("height", 36)
        .attr("rx", 5).attr("fill", isActive ? "#243250" : "#1e2535")
        .attr("stroke", isActive ? "#7c9eff" : "#2e3a52").attr("stroke-width", 1.5);
      svg.append("text").attr("x", x + slotW / 2).attr("y", top - 8).attr("text-anchor", "middle")
        .attr("fill", "#606880").attr("font-size", 11).text(i);
      slots[i].forEach((k, j) => {
        const cy = top + 40 + j * 36;
        const isNew = k === newKey && i === activeSlot;
        svg.append("rect").attr("x", x).attr("y", cy).attr("width", slotW).attr("height", 30)
          .attr("rx", 5).attr("fill", isNew ? "#6ee7a8" : "#3a4d80")
          .attr("stroke", isNew ? "#6ee7a8" : "#4a5680");
        svg.append("text").attr("x", x + slotW / 2).attr("y", cy + 20).attr("text-anchor", "middle")
          .attr("fill", isNew ? "#0d1117" : "#cbd5f0").attr("font-size", 12).attr("font-weight", "600").text(k);
        if (j === 0) svg.append("line").attr("x1", x + slotW / 2).attr("y1", top + 36).attr("x2", x + slotW / 2).attr("y2", cy).attr("stroke", "#2e3a52");
        else svg.append("line").attr("x1", x + slotW / 2).attr("y1", cy - 6).attr("x2", x + slotW / 2).attr("y2", cy).attr("stroke", "#2e3a52");
      });
    }
    document.getElementById("hash-alpha").textContent =
      `Load factor α = n/m = ${n}/${M} = ${(n / M).toFixed(2)}`;
  }

  function reset() {
    slots = Array.from({ length: M }, () => []);
    n = 0;
    draw();
    document.getElementById("hash-log").textContent = "Table cleared. Enter a key and press Insert.";
  }

  document.getElementById("hash-insert").addEventListener("click", function () {
    const k = parseInt(document.getElementById("hash-key").value, 10);
    if (isNaN(k)) return;
    const slot = ((k % M) + M) % M;
    const collision = slots[slot].length > 0;
    slots[slot].push(k);
    n++;
    draw(slot, k);
    document.getElementById("hash-log").textContent =
      `h(${k}) = ${k} mod ${M} = ${slot}. ` +
      (collision ? `Slot ${slot} occupied → chained (chain length now ${slots[slot].length}).` : `Slot ${slot} was empty → placed directly.`);
  });
  document.getElementById("hash-reset").addEventListener("click", reset);
  reset();
})();
</script>
